      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The urgency of climate change makes nuclear expansion a necessary, albeit not sufficient, component of any realistic net-zero strategy. While renewables are critical, they currently lack the consistent baseload capacity and grid stability that nuclear provides, making a complete transition to renewables alone technically and economically unfeasible. Therefore, a balanced approach that heavily integrates nuclear energy alongside renewables is the most pragmatic path forward to meet global climate goals.",
